![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3b28158b-b91a-4ffc-b55a-81086a45cb9c/ep305.jpg)

Right in the eye of the hurricane which is the tumultuous state of the current MCU, a movie was released that has both audiences and critics divided. The Marvels starring Brie Larson, Teyonah Paris, and Iman Vellani is the 33rd film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe but is it any good? Join us as we do our best to recap The Marvels, the implication of its post-credit scene, and the future of Marvel in general on this exciting episode of Major Issues!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

